1
00:00:11,100 --> 00:00:13,667
<i>Please tell me what to do
so you can forgive me, Olive.</i>

2
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,500
<i> I'll take your offer on that.</i>

3
00:00:15,633 --> 00:00:16,833
<i> Find Emma.</i>

4
00:00:16,967 --> 00:00:18,600
<i> Poor Mookie.</i>

5
00:00:18,733 --> 00:00:19,767
<i> She has no mother.</i>

6
00:00:19,900 --> 00:00:23,267
<i>And even her grandmother
is missing in action.</i>

7
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,233
<i>I want to check
what that noise is.</i>

8
00:00:25,367 --> 00:00:26,233
<i> Then let's check it.</i>

9
00:00:26,367 --> 00:00:28,467
<i>We have lots of rats
in our basement.</i>

10
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:32,633
<i>Did you check if the people
who adopted us were good?</i>

11
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:35,100
<i> Dear, I'm begging you.</i>

12
00:00:35,267 --> 00:00:36,300
<i> Shut up!</i>

13
00:00:36,433 --> 00:00:39,900
<i>Every punch you throw,
be it a jab or a kick,</i>

14
00:00:40,033 --> 00:00:41,500
<i> must come from within.</i>

15
00:00:41,633 --> 00:00:45,200
<i>So you can show
what you're fighting for.</i>

16
00:00:45,333 --> 00:00:47,100
<i> Give me five days to find her.</i>

17
00:00:47,233 --> 00:00:48,733
<i>Why did you hire someone
to look for Emma?</i>

18
00:00:48,867 --> 00:00:50,300
<i> I just want closure.</i>

19
00:00:50,433 --> 00:00:51,633
<i> That's all I want.</i>

20
00:01:29,567 --> 00:01:30,667
What the hell!

21
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:32,400
Let go of me!

22
00:01:41,467 --> 00:01:42,767
Help!

23
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:45,133
Let go of me! Help!

24
00:01:45,267 --> 00:01:47,200
Help!

25
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:07,367
Mom!

26
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,800
- That's Mookie!
- That's Mookie!

27
00:02:10,933 --> 00:02:12,033
Come on!

28
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:17,700
- Dear?
- Mookie?

29
00:02:17,833 --> 00:02:18,700
Mookie!

30
00:02:18,833 --> 00:02:20,100
What happened to you?

31
00:02:20,233 --> 00:02:23,733
Dad! Something bad happened
to Mom.

32
00:02:23,867 --> 00:02:25,067
Relax, baby girl.

33
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:26,667
It's just a bad dream.

34
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,933
- Yes.
- I know, Auntie Jade.

35
00:02:30,133 --> 00:02:33,833
But I can't help
but worry for Mom.

36
00:02:35,100 --> 00:02:39,633
My heart felt so tight
while seeing her getting hurt.

37
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:45,000
And I hate myself for feeling
this way.

38
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:48,733
But it pains me.

39
00:02:59,433 --> 00:03:01,700
Don't worry, baby girl.

40
00:03:01,833 --> 00:03:07,233
I'm sure your mom is happy
wherever she is.

41
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:13,400
She never came back for you,
remember?

42
00:03:14,433 --> 00:03:15,467
But, Auntie Jade,

43
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:18,867
what if my dream is real?

44
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:21,733
What if she really needs help?

45
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:24,400
What if something bad
happened to her?

46
00:03:25,467 --> 00:03:28,000
That's enough.
Stop overthinking.

47
00:03:28,133 --> 00:03:29,800
I'm sure she's fine.

48
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,500
<i> Damn you, Emma!</i>

49
00:03:34,633 --> 00:03:37,833
<i>Why don't you leave
my family alone?</i>

50
00:03:37,967 --> 00:03:39,900
<i> Show up to Altair!</i>

51
00:03:40,033 --> 00:03:42,367
<i>So he can remove you
from our lives.</i>

52
00:03:59,667 --> 00:04:02,933
I talked to Mrs. Ramirez
of Ramirez Lab.

53
00:04:03,067 --> 00:04:07,567
And she told me there was
an agreement last year

54
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:10,300
that Artemis Pharmacy would
spearhead the product launch

55
00:04:10,433 --> 00:04:14,433
of their multivitamin brand,
Activora.

56
00:04:14,567 --> 00:04:17,900
She doesn't know I'm Olive.

57
00:04:19,333 --> 00:04:23,367
I invested in the research
development of that product.

58
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:27,400
Because I want to be part
of a phenomenal product

59
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:30,933
that will change people's
lifestyles and improve

60
00:04:31,067 --> 00:04:32,900
their quality of life.

61
00:04:33,033 --> 00:04:39,133
People will have time for their
family despite being so busy.

62
00:04:39,267 --> 00:04:41,867
Is it because your parents
had no time for you?

63
00:04:42,967 --> 00:04:46,067
Because that's how
I am with Mookie.

64
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:50,500
I spent all my life on her.

65
00:04:50,633 --> 00:04:55,567
But someone suddenly
took her away from me.

66
00:04:56,700 --> 00:05:00,100
Good thing she's with me again.

67
00:05:00,233 --> 00:05:05,000
That's why I still want
to handle that launch myself.

68
00:05:05,167 --> 00:05:08,767
And I appreciate that
you're helping me run

69
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:13,000
Artemis Pharmacy
and other things.

70
00:05:13,133 --> 00:05:14,367
Of course.

71
00:05:16,467 --> 00:05:18,967
Ma'am, excuse me.
You have a visitor.

72
00:05:24,433 --> 00:05:25,833
Altair, any update?

73
00:05:28,167 --> 00:05:29,167
Emma's dead.

74
00:05:30,367 --> 00:05:31,800
She's not coming back anymore.

75
00:05:31,933 --> 00:05:32,900
What?

76
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:37,167
Emma's dead?

77
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,100
This is where I buried her.

78
00:06:28,733 --> 00:06:29,967
Tell me, Altair.

79
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,400
How did you kill Emma?

80
00:06:36,367 --> 00:06:41,867
I covered her head with plastic
until she ran out of breath.

81
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:50,400
Here's her picture
before I buried her.

82
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,500
That's enough, Altair.

83
00:06:55,633 --> 00:06:56,633
Good job.

84
00:06:59,100 --> 00:07:01,100
Congratulations, Olive.

85
00:07:01,233 --> 00:07:03,433
No one's getting
in your way now.

86
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:11,167
Thank you.

87
00:07:13,267 --> 00:07:15,967
Leave me and my sister for now.

88
00:07:17,667 --> 00:07:18,733
Let's go.

89
00:08:05,967 --> 00:08:08,533
Hello, my dear sister, Emma.

90
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:18,733
I hope that you rest...

91
00:08:24,767 --> 00:08:26,200
No, no, no.

92
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:33,367
I don't want you
to rest in peace.

93
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:38,667
Because you don't deserve that.

94
00:08:44,067 --> 00:08:45,300
I hope...

95
00:08:48,033 --> 00:08:52,100
that you rot in hell.

96
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:14,033
Dear.

97
00:11:17,733 --> 00:11:19,867
I can go home by myself.

98
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:20,933
Dear, I don't like this.

99
00:11:21,067 --> 00:11:23,300
I don't like it when we fight.

100
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:27,500
Your Aunt Jade called.

101
00:11:27,633 --> 00:11:29,333
She's on her way here.

102
00:11:29,467 --> 00:11:31,700
She said she had something
important to tell us.

103
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:39,767
Mookie, don't get mad at me,
please.

104
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:43,900
Let's stop fighting.

105
00:11:44,967 --> 00:11:45,933
Love!

106
00:11:46,067 --> 00:11:48,833
I'm so sorry.
Hi, baby girl.

107
00:11:48,967 --> 00:11:51,233
I'm sorry I'm late.

108
00:11:51,367 --> 00:11:55,000
I met with the private
investigator.

109
00:11:55,133 --> 00:11:57,400
He has news about Emma.

110
00:11:57,533 --> 00:11:59,833
So you still hire him
to find Emma?

111
00:11:59,967 --> 00:12:01,733
I'm so sorry, love.

112
00:12:01,867 --> 00:12:05,767
I feel restless that I know
nothing about my sister.

113
00:12:09,133 --> 00:12:10,200
And here's the thing.

114
00:12:12,267 --> 00:12:13,400
Unfortunately...

115
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:16,567
Emma's not coming back.

116
00:12:19,333 --> 00:12:21,700
She went with another man.

117
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:22,900
- What?
- What?

118
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:24,033
I know.

119
00:12:25,367 --> 00:12:26,333
I'm so sorry.

120
00:12:27,633 --> 00:12:30,567
But that's what the private
investigator found out.

121
00:12:30,700 --> 00:12:33,233
And you know what?
It makes a lot of sense.

122
00:12:34,433 --> 00:12:37,567
She left because she went
with another man.

123
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:41,267
She would've come back to us
if she hadn't done that.

124
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:44,367
She would've shown up to us
a long time ago, right?

125
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:45,633
But no.

126
00:12:47,633 --> 00:12:52,000
Maybe it's about time
we should accept

127
00:12:52,167 --> 00:12:53,600
that Emma's no longer
coming back.

128
00:12:54,833 --> 00:12:56,300
She's never coming back...

129
00:12:57,867 --> 00:12:58,967
ever.

130
00:13:10,767 --> 00:13:12,533
I told you, Emma.

131
00:13:14,333 --> 00:13:17,233
I told you to stick with me.

132
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:21,467
But son of a gun.
You still left without me.

133
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:24,733
Look what happened to you.

134
00:13:28,533 --> 00:13:31,033
So, Mom really has abandoned us.

135
00:13:34,933 --> 00:13:37,567
Let's stop hoping
she'll come back.

136
00:13:38,933 --> 00:13:41,600
- I'm sorry, dear. Mookie!
- Love, love.

137
00:13:41,733 --> 00:13:44,233
Let Mookie be for now.

138
00:13:44,367 --> 00:13:47,267
Let her process.
Let her grieve.

139
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:51,033
It won't help if we keep
following her.

140
00:13:51,167 --> 00:13:52,867
I'm sure she's going to be fine.

141
00:14:02,533 --> 00:14:03,567
That's enough, Boss.

142
00:14:04,467 --> 00:14:06,067
Don't you feel chills?

143
00:14:07,933 --> 00:14:10,033
I can't believe it.

144
00:14:12,567 --> 00:14:16,667
Don't I look dead
in that picture?

145
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:26,233
So, please don't get mad
that I left without you.

146
00:14:26,367 --> 00:14:28,267
Nothing bad happened to me.

147
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:33,733
Good thing Marco and I
sensed it.

148
00:14:33,867 --> 00:14:36,733
But wow.

149
00:14:37,967 --> 00:14:39,900
This picture is impressive.

150
00:14:40,033 --> 00:14:43,133
I can't believe
we pulled this off.

151
00:14:43,267 --> 00:14:45,067
- It looks so real.
- Right?

152
00:14:46,233 --> 00:14:48,833
I actually felt chills
when I saw that picture.

153
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:52,233
Our plan was successful.

154
00:14:55,233 --> 00:14:58,167
This wouldn't happen
without your support.

155
00:14:58,300 --> 00:14:59,567
So, thank you.

156
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:03,000
You're very much welcome.

157
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:07,600
But remember, this is all you.

158
00:15:07,733 --> 00:15:11,533
We only support you.

159
00:15:11,667 --> 00:15:14,900
<i>We must know Jade's every move.</i>

160
00:15:15,033 --> 00:15:18,233
<i>So we can strategize
how I can haunt her.</i>

161
00:15:18,367 --> 00:15:20,100
<i>I thought of suggesting it,
too, Boss.</i>

162
00:15:21,267 --> 00:15:22,567
<i> Oh, really?</i>

163
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:27,033
<i> Keep an eye on Jade.</i>

164
00:15:27,167 --> 00:15:28,733
<i> Know her every schedule.</i>

165
00:15:31,433 --> 00:15:32,300
<i> Yes, Boss.</i>

166
00:15:32,433 --> 00:15:33,467
<i> Emma.</i>

167
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,700
<i>The people Jade is talking
to look suspicious.</i>

168
00:15:35,867 --> 00:15:37,367
<i>They seem like high-class goons.</i>

169
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:39,100
<i>She even handed him
a picture of you.</i>

170
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:43,333
<i>Are you just a private
investigator?</i>

171
00:15:43,467 --> 00:15:45,967
<i>Actually, he's not just
a good investigator.</i>

172
00:15:47,267 --> 00:15:48,400
<i> He's also a good...</i>

173
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:50,600
<i> hitman.</i>

174
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:54,567
<i> Good.</i>

175
00:15:56,267 --> 00:16:00,500
<i>Once you find Emma,
I want you to get rid of her.</i>

176
00:16:01,867 --> 00:16:03,667
<i>She's getting in the way
of my plans.</i>

177
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:07,200
<i> Besides...</i>

178
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:09,033
<i> Mookie has only one mother.</i>

179
00:16:10,867 --> 00:16:12,767
<i> And that's me.</i>

180
00:16:12,900 --> 00:16:15,233
<i>I'm sure she's planning
something bad against me.</i>

181
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:18,367
<i> The man Jade hired is leaving.</i>

182
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:19,533
<i> I'll call you again.</i>

183
00:16:19,667 --> 00:16:20,800
<i> You know what to do.</i>

184
00:16:20,933 --> 00:16:21,933
<i> Be safe.</i>

185
00:16:23,433 --> 00:16:26,300
<i>What will you do
if Jade does that to you?</i>

186
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,300
<i> Presence of mind.</i>

187
00:16:29,433 --> 00:16:32,100
<i>Your first reaction is to panic.</i>

188
00:16:32,233 --> 00:16:34,933
<i>The first thing you should do
is to step on her foot.</i>

189
00:16:40,733 --> 00:16:41,900
<i> Let go of me!</i>

190
00:16:42,067 --> 00:16:44,300
<i>You'll give it all
your strength.</i>

191
00:16:44,433 --> 00:16:48,033
<i>You will use the anger you feel
towards Jade.</i>

192
00:16:48,167 --> 00:16:49,300
<i> Help!</i>

193
00:16:49,433 --> 00:16:51,200
<i> You will elbow my side.</i>

194
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:52,600
<i> A strong one.</i>

195
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,533
<i> What if she doesn't let go?</i>

196
00:16:57,667 --> 00:17:02,333
<i>You will introduce your elbow
to her jaw or nose</i>

197
00:17:02,467 --> 00:17:04,633
<i> to expose her weakness.</i>

198
00:17:16,233 --> 00:17:17,233
<i> Help!</i>

199
00:17:17,367 --> 00:17:22,000
<i> Remember, a waris a mind game.</i>

200
00:17:22,133 --> 00:17:23,267
<i> You must strike first.</i>

201
00:17:29,433 --> 00:17:30,400
How are you?

202
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,633
I remember what happened.

203
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:38,467
What if I got killed?

204
00:17:40,133 --> 00:17:41,600
What if the man Jade hired
killed me?

205
00:17:41,733 --> 00:17:43,400
What would happen to Mookie
if I died?

206
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:47,467
Marco, water.

207
00:17:52,533 --> 00:17:53,533
Listen to me.

208
00:17:55,133 --> 00:17:56,533
I'm with you now.

209
00:17:56,667 --> 00:17:57,833
You're safe.

210
00:17:59,067 --> 00:18:00,933
Jade failed.

211
00:18:02,133 --> 00:18:03,967
So take a deep breath.

212
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:04,700
Okay?

213
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:07,833
Breathe in, breathe out.

214
00:18:07,967 --> 00:18:09,433
Okay?

215
00:18:09,567 --> 00:18:12,733
Now, go back to your plan.

216
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:16,800
Your plan to haunt Jade.

217
00:18:16,933 --> 00:18:19,233
We'll ruin her plan.

218
00:18:19,367 --> 00:18:22,233
All of her plans!
We'll drive her crazy!

219
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:25,200
So that no one will believe her

220
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:29,067
once you expose the truth
about what she did to you.

221
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:30,633
Now, think about it.

222
00:18:32,233 --> 00:18:34,700
Who are you doing this for?

223
00:18:34,833 --> 00:18:35,833
Tell me.

224
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:40,800
- I'm doing this for Mookie.
- For Mookie.

225
00:18:40,933 --> 00:18:42,767
So you can take Mookie back.

226
00:18:49,367 --> 00:18:51,167
Gather all your anger
towards Jade.

227
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:55,400
Consider yourself the winner.

228
00:18:55,567 --> 00:18:57,133
Darn you, Jade.

229
00:18:57,267 --> 00:19:01,100
If you think you've won,
you're mistaken.

230
00:19:04,967 --> 00:19:07,100
Logan,

231
00:19:07,233 --> 00:19:10,000
I'm sorry that you're getting
dragged into my mess.

232
00:19:10,133 --> 00:19:12,467
I wanted to get dragged
into this.

233
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:15,933
Because I want to help
you get even with Jade

234
00:19:16,067 --> 00:19:17,267
and take Mookie back.

235
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:19,967
Are you ready to face him again?

236
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:26,467
Logan!

237
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:27,367
He's here.

238
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:29,567
Let him in.

239
00:19:58,467 --> 00:20:00,000
<i> Wake up.</i>

240
00:20:00,133 --> 00:20:01,333
<i> Don't!</i>

241
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:02,833
<i> I said wake up!</i>

242
00:20:16,033 --> 00:20:18,600
<i> Why do you want to abduct me?</i>

243
00:20:18,733 --> 00:20:20,100
<i> What did Jade tell you to do?</i>

244
00:20:21,633 --> 00:20:22,700
<i> Answer her.</i>

245
00:20:40,233 --> 00:20:41,267
<i> Plan B.</i>

246
00:20:45,033 --> 00:20:46,833
<i> Sorry, I have to do this.</i>

247
00:21:03,067 --> 00:21:05,533
<i> What did you do to my family?</i>

248
00:21:05,667 --> 00:21:07,767
<i>So you've finally spoken,
you bastard.</i>

249
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:11,067
<i> We didn't do anything to them.</i>

250
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:15,833
<i>Well, we haven't done
anything yet.</i>

251
00:21:15,967 --> 00:21:20,067
<i>But we've done something
to you already.</i>

252
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:26,533
<i>So you're a model husband
and father to your family.</i>

253
00:21:28,333 --> 00:21:31,000
<i> Your kids look up to you.</i>

254
00:21:31,133 --> 00:21:34,900
<i> But poor children.</i>

255
00:21:35,033 --> 00:21:37,500
<i>Looks like they're going
to lose their idol.</i>

256
00:21:37,633 --> 00:21:39,700
<i> Jade wants Emma dead.</i>

257
00:21:46,567 --> 00:21:48,267
Jade wants Emma dead.

258
00:21:48,767 --> 00:21:50,400
Jade's crazy.

259
00:21:50,967 --> 00:21:52,133
She's a demon.

260
00:21:53,167 --> 00:21:54,600
Please, don't kill me.

261
00:21:54,733 --> 00:21:56,000
My kids are still young.

262
00:21:56,500 --> 00:21:58,000
I can kill Jade if you like.

263
00:22:01,867 --> 00:22:04,667
It's so easy for you
to kill someone.

264
00:22:05,333 --> 00:22:07,667
But you're afraid to die.

265
00:22:08,333 --> 00:22:10,000
You're a bastard.

266
00:22:10,133 --> 00:22:11,533
What do you want me to do?

267
00:22:13,267 --> 00:22:15,233
Just tell me.
What do I do?

268
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:18,200
Convince Jade
that you killed me.

269
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,433
Keep the end of your bargain.

270
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:48,000
Make sure my family's safe.

271
00:22:52,667 --> 00:22:54,267
Don't worry.

272
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:56,033
We didn't hurt them.

273
00:22:58,400 --> 00:22:59,533
We don't do that.

274
00:23:00,667 --> 00:23:04,367
They're staying in Hem Till
Resort in Laguna.

275
00:23:05,533 --> 00:23:07,667
We made it appear
that you surprised them.

276
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:09,900
And that you'll follow
them there.

277
00:23:10,033 --> 00:23:13,000
Did you think we brought them
in a stockroom?

278
00:23:13,133 --> 00:23:14,567
Tied and tortured?

279
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:17,467
We don't hurt children.

280
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:20,167
I also have a kid.

281
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:23,600
And she's with the monster
who told you to kill me.

282
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:51,267
Love.

283
00:23:52,567 --> 00:23:57,233
Don't worry too much
about Mookie.

284
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:58,400
She's fine.

285
00:23:58,533 --> 00:24:01,333
I've talked to her,
and she just wants some space.

286
00:24:03,067 --> 00:24:08,300
Does your private investigator
know the man Emma went with?

287
00:24:09,733 --> 00:24:11,367
Does he know where they went?

288
00:24:14,733 --> 00:24:16,100
Why do you ask?

289
00:24:20,033 --> 00:24:21,300
Why do you want to know

290
00:24:21,433 --> 00:24:24,233
if the private investigator
knows where Emma is?

291
00:24:26,100 --> 00:24:27,867
Is it because you want
to see her?

292
00:24:29,233 --> 00:24:31,033
Jade, I won't lie to you.

293
00:24:32,300 --> 00:24:34,100
I really want to see Emma.

294
00:24:34,233 --> 00:24:36,533
I want to clarify
so many things with her.

295
00:24:37,500 --> 00:24:38,467
What?

296
00:24:46,633 --> 00:24:47,700
Hold her.

297
00:24:47,967 --> 00:24:50,500
Hey! What are you doing?

298
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:52,733
Stop!
Leave me alone!

299
00:24:52,867 --> 00:24:56,033
Say hi! We're live!

300
00:24:56,167 --> 00:24:57,233
What the heck!

301
00:24:59,633 --> 00:25:03,700
Imagine it as your enemy.

302
00:25:03,867 --> 00:25:06,733
And you need to protect
yourself.

303
00:25:06,867 --> 00:25:08,533
Emma's not coming back anymore.

304
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:12,067
So if I were you,

305
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:14,433
I wouldn't waste my time on her.

306
00:25:18,100 --> 00:25:19,267
What's that?
